args: What an incredibly fun show that was!
Where do you want to go next, Tiki?
There's a great spot where you can\nsee some pretty scenery right here!
My goodness, so many people... Oooo!\nLet's check out that cafe, Big Sis!
Those baked goods DO look delicious...
Man, she's really takin' this more\nseriously than I thought.
It's like we are witnessing an\nentirely new side of Mym.
And Tiki is clearly quite attached to...\nOh dear. Something seems amiss.
I told you, I'm fine! Don't worry about me!
Uh oh. Looks like trouble in sisterville.
I didn't DO anything! I just invited her\nto go somewhere like always!
She was always happy to travel before\nand even invited me places, but now...
The strange thing was, I felt like she\nDID want to go somewhere with you.
Has aught changed between you two?
I don't know. I don't think so?
I'm going to check on Tiki.
Maybe you should leave this to me.
All right, darling. If you think it best.
Mind if I sit next to you?
No. I mean...she didn't do anything wrong.
I was wrong. I just... I got lonely.
I used to think about Mar-Mar and Ban-Ban\nand it would make me lonely.
But once I had people in my life again—\nonce I had Mym—it was all good.
But I know we're going to have to be\nseparated someday, and thinking about\nthat makes me lonely all over again.
And the more I make happy memories\nwith Mym, the bigger that feeling of\nloneliness becomes. It...scares me.
Does Mym know about any of this?
No. I thought it would upset her,\nso I didn't say anything.
I'm actually a little brother AND a big one,\nso I think I understand how you both feel.
I get the feeling of not wanting to trouble\nyour older siblings, as well as wanting\nyour little sister to tell you everything.
Maybe that's just what it means\nto have a sibling.
So why not tell Mym your worries?
I'm sure she'll accept and understand\nthem—she's really enthusiastic about\nbeing your older sister, after all.
Maybe I was a bad sister...
Because I ran off in a huff\ninstead of talking to you.
I love being with you. It's SO fun!
But...I was getting lonely thinking\nabout how I'd have to leave you.
It was like the more fun we had,\nthe more lonely I felt. And...
I'm just glad you don't hate me.
Of COURSE I don't hate you!
Well then, it's my turn to apologize.
I also get lonely when I think about\nhaving to say goodbye to you.
That's why I wanted to make\nas many memories as possible\nwhile we had the chance.
That way I wouldn't be as sad\nwhen you had to go away.
*sigh* It's been a while since I've felt\nlonely like this. But it's always been my\nnature.
I guess we're alike in that way, huh?
Yeah! It's funny, though—when I\ntalk to you, my loneliness vanishes.
Same here. I guess we should've\ntalked to each other sooner!
Then from now on, the two of us\nwill stop worrying on our own.
When sisters share the weight of their\nsadness, it increases their happiness!
And that's why our goodbye won't hurt\nso much—because we'll be all full up\nwith that happiness.
I'm glad you were able to be\nmy little sister, Tiki.
And I'm glad I have you, too!\nOh, but wait...
Oh no! Did you just remember\nsomething I did wrong?!
No, that's not it! It's just... Um...
Can I try being the big sister next?
Only if you promise to spoil me\nevery chance you get!
Sound like a plan, Big Sis?
Oh, I can't wait! We're going to\nDOUBLE our sister memories!
